        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b3,
        dcat:Dataset,
        systemmap:MasterData ;
    rdfs:label "UID"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """
        Every company active in Switzerland receives a unique Business Identification Number (UID).
        The use of the UID facilitates administrative relief for companies and enables more efficient collaboration between authorities.
        """@en ;
    systemmap:containedIn systemmap:SuEtT7joC8HXVSfF .

systemmap:SDmJeWK7EOnMqRLs a _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b1,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b2,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b3,
        dcat:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "Conditions for the Use of Plant Protection Products"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """
        Regulations and restrictions to be observed when using plant protection products, including dosage, application timing, and protective measures.
        """@en ;
    systemmap:containedIn systemmap:Shhoiq8azX3SHGL3W .

systemmap:SDqb9NPoB6n3MZf2 a _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b1,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b2,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b3,
        dcat:Dataset,
        termdat:52451,
        termdat:52453 ;
    rdfs:label "Reductions in direct payments"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf systemmap:SQ2MIhpz1CvdqK6f ;
    rdfs:comment """  
        Contains information on the regulations and procedures by which direct payments to agricultural enterprises are reduced.  
        The data includes criteria, calculation bases, affected periods, and administrative processes that may lead to such reductions.  
        """@en .

systemmap:SEI0Jp1SabxWUiGh0 a _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b1,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b2,
        _:n0e42f29d9d46439699142ff381caea57b3,
        dcat:Dataset,
        systemmap:MasterData ;
    rdfs:label "ATDB Number"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf systemmap:SAUWzyCpeGZ6vVil ;
    rdfs:comment """
        The ATDB Number is a farm number assigned in the Animal Traffic Database (ATDB) for animal husbandry in Switzerland, in particular for cattle, pigs, sheep, goats, and game kept in enclosures. 
        It is used to uniquely identify locations with animals relevant to animal diseases and to trace animals. 
        The ATDB Number is permanently linked to the cantonal farm number (KT_ID_B) and is therefore location-specific.
        """@en .

