        dcat:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "Global plant list"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """
        List of all possible plant species with corresponding plant species codes.
        UPOV uses a specific coding system to uniquely identify plant species and genera.
        These so-called UPOV codes usually consist of five letters for the genus and three letters for the species. For example, <tt>PRUNU_ARM</tt> stands for <i>Prunus armeniaca</i> (apricot).
        This system facilitates the classification and exchange of information on plant varieties.
        """@en ;
