systemmap:SFKPRpdGa5UISiJlx a schema:GovernmentOrganization,
        schema:Organization,
        systemmap:FederalOrganization ;
    rdfs:label "Federal Office for Customs and Border Security"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """  
        The Federal Office for Customs and Border Security is the largest administrative unit of the Ministry of Finance, with over 4,000 employees.  
        FOCBS experts check whether goods are properly declared, determine taxes and duties, and ensure compliance with numerous regulations to protect the population and economy.  
        Together with national and international partner authorities, FOCBS also carries out security and migration-related tasks at borders, in rail transport, and at airports.  
        """@en ;
    owl:sameAs staatskalender:10008659 ;
    systemmap:abbreviation "FOCBS"@en ;
    systemmap:operates systemmap:S7u1Bh6qfXUbSDkv .

